author: Ryan Dube
title: Ecuador Leftist Leads Presidential Vote, but Runoff Appears Likely - WSJ
text:
Ecuadoreans waited anxiously on Monday for official results from the vote to replace President Rafael Correa, as pollsters, political analysts and the opposition predicted the presidential election would go to a runoff while allies of the leftist ruling party candidate said a first-round victory was within reach.
